  },
  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "U3D (ECMA-363) binary block structure: magic 'U3D\\x00'(4B) + major_version(int16 LE) + minor_version(uint16 LE) + File_Header_Block(type=0x00443355, data_length, meta_length, profile_id, declaration_size, file_size(uint64 LE), character_encoding(106=UTF-8), unit_scaling(float64 LE)). Then Modifier Chain blocks: each block = block_type(uint32) + data_length(uint32) + meta_data_length(uint32) + data + metadata. Key block types: 0x00FFFFFF=File_Header, 0xFFFFFF00=Modifier_Chain, 0xFFFFFF14=Priority_Update, 0x00003000=Group_Node, 0x00003100=Model_Node, 0x00003200=Light_Node, 0x00003300=View_Node, 0x00100000=CLOD_Mesh_Generator(Declaration), 0x00100001=CLOD_Base_Mesh_Continuation, 0x00100002=CLOD_Progressive_Mesh_Continuation. CLOD mesh: positions(float32[3]), normals, faces. Textures embedded as JPEG or PNG data in texture blocks.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Bytes 0-3: 'U3D\\x00' magic confirms ECMA-363 format",
      "Bytes 4-5: major version (int16 LE), bytes 6-7: minor version (uint16 LE)",
      "Offset 8: File Header Block begins — block_type 0x00443355, then profile_id and file_size",
      "Search for block type 0x00100000 (CLOD Mesh Generator) for 3D geometry data"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
